H0.text: Nervous is the body system that includes the esophagus, stomach, and small intestine.

H1.text: Digestive is the body system that includes the esophagus, stomach, and small intestine.

H2.text: Respiratory is the body system that includes the esophagus, stomach, and small intestine.

H3.text: Muscular is the body system that includes the esophagus, stomach, and small intestine.

A4.text: The human digestive system consists of the gastrointestinal tract plus the accessory organs of digestion (the tongue, salivary glands, pancreas, liver, and gallbladder).

A5.text: The largest structure of the digestive system is the GI tract.
